It is also a responsibility of the 
New South Wales Government. 

3
00:00:08.520 --> 00:00:13.220 line:15 align:center
Accessibility is grounded in international, 
Commonwealth and state laws. 

4
00:00:13.520 --> 00:00:18.520 line:15 align:center
The Commonwealth Anti-Discrimination Act 
and Disability Discrimination Act 

5
00:00:18.820 --> 00:00:22.820 line:15 align:center
and the New South Wales Disability 
Inclusion Act all mark milestones 

6
00:00:23.120 --> 00:00:25.120 line:15 align:center
towards inclusivity and equality.

7
00:00:25.320 --> 00:00:30.120 line:15 align:center
Australia is a signatory of the 
UN Convention on the Rights of Persons 

8
00:00:30.220 --> 00:00:34.120 line:15 align:center
with Disabilities, committing us to 
making our work accessible for people 

9
00:00:34.220 --> 00:00:35.220 line:15 align:center
with disability. 

10
00:00:36.220 --> 00:00:40.120 line:15 align:center
The Commonwealth Disability Discrimination 
Act also states it's unlawful to 

11
00:00:40.320 --> 00:00:42.320 line:15 align:center
discriminate based on disability.

12
00:00:42.520 --> 00:00:47.820 line:15 align:center
Accessibility is a standard guided by 
the Australian standard on accessibility

13
00:00:47.970 --> 00:00:49.820 line:15 align:center
and W3C web guidelines. 

14
00:00:50.220 --> 00:00:55.320 line:15 align:center
The New South Wales Government strives 
to ensure accessible ICT products and services.

15
00:00:55.820 --> 00:01:00.820 line:15 align:center
As New South Wales Government staff, 
it's essential to consider accessibility 

16
00:01:01.120 --> 00:01:02.520 line:15 align:center
in your daily work tasks. 

17
00:01:02.920 --> 00:01:07.120 line:15 align:center
Every cluster has its own New South Wales 
Disability Inclusion Action Plan, 

18
00:01:07.420 --> 00:01:11.120 line:15 align:center
and it is our obligation to ensure that 
our digital products and services 

19
00:01:11.520 --> 00:01:12.920 line:15 align:center
are accessible to everyone.